cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the capacity of vehicular networks with infrastructure support and proposes a cooperative communication strategy to improve the capacity. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper develops an analytical framework to model the data dissemination process and obtain a closed form expression of the achievable capacity. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper considers a delay-tolerant application scenario with large-size file downloads. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a potential category as the paper discusses the inter-play of multiple factors including vehicle-to-infrastructure communications, vehicle-to-vehicle communications, density and mobility of vehicles, and cooperation among vehicles and infrastructure. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security and privacy issues in vehicular networks.
